        "title": "Add Zed provider with dashboard token billing and fix split-mode menu bar placement",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- **Zed provider (phase 1):** Keychain API token auth via `GET /client/users/me` for plan, edit predictions, and billing cycle metadata.\n- **Zed provider (phase 2, experimental):** Optional dashboard cookie import (`zed.session`) with `GET /frontend/billing/usage` for live token spend; cookie source defaults to **Off**.\n- **Menu bar placement:** Seed and repair split-mode `codexbar-*` `NSStatusItem Preferred Position` keys so newly enabled providers (e.g. Zed) cluster with other CodexBar icons left of system status items instead of landing beside Control Center / AirPods.\n- Tests, fixtures, and [`docs/zed.md`](docs/zed.md).\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `make check`\n- [x] `swift test --filter Zed`\n- [x] `swift test --filter Placement`\n- [ ] Enable Zed in split mode with multiple providers; confirm all CodexBar icons are grouped together and sit left of system menu bar items\n- [ ] Toggle Zed off/on (or enable a fresh provider) and confirm placement seeding for the new `codexbar-*` autosave name\n- [ ] With a Zed API token in Keychain, verify plan and edit-prediction windows in the menu card\n- [ ] (Optional) Import `zed.session` cookie manually and confirm live token billing windows update\n\n## CHANGELOG\n\nUnder **0.35.1 — Unreleased**:\n\n- **Added:** Zed provider with Keychain API token billing and optional dashboard cookie usage tracking.\n- **Fixed:** Split-mode menu bar icon grouping for newly enabled `codexbar-*` status items.\n\nMade with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)",
